## Context

Transformers.js already supports `image-to-text` (encoder-decoder caption models) and
`document-question-answering` (image + structured prompt → text), but has no pipeline for
modern **decoder-only vision-language models** (LLaVA, SmolVLM, PaliGemma, etc.) that take
an image _and_ a free-form text prompt and generate a response. The model class
`AutoModelForImageTextToText` already exists in `src/models.js` (line 8736) and maps to all
the right architectures — the only missing piece is the pipeline layer on top of it.

The task is to add the new `image-text-to-text` pipeline without touching any existing
pipeline class or its behavior.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/pipelines.js` | All pipeline classes + `SUPPORTED_TASKS` registry + `pipeline()` factory |
